FBIS4-355 "drafr068_a_94015" FBIS-AFR-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda Kigali Erupts in Violence; Ministers Killed Kigali Erupts in Violence; Ministers Killed `At Least' 22 Clergy Killed AU0804105594 Paris AFP in English 1033 GMT 8 Apr 94 AU0804105594 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Paris, April 8 (AFP) -- At least 22 priests and nuns have been killed in Rwanda since clashes began there Thursday [7 April], church officials said Friday in Kigali, reached by telephone from Paris. Six priests and nine nuns were killed in Kigali itself and six priests and a nun in the town of Nyundo, in the northwest province of Gisenye, the official at the papal nuncio's office said.
